Luanda &mdash; The Fortress of S&atilde;o Francisco do Penedo in Luanda will be restored and equipped at a total cost equivalent in Kwanzas to more than 37 million US dollars.Pursuant to a Presidential Decree No. 130/17, of June 12, the construction company Mota-Engil Angola will carry out the restoration and equipping of the monument.In 1992, the former Department of State for Culture had classified the Fortress of S&atilde;o Francisco do Penedo, also known as Military Reclusion House, as National Historical-Cultural Heritage.